## Rules

- One entry per distinct audit report, newest first.
- `auditor`: firm name, e.g. `Certora`, `Trail of Bits`, `OpenZeppelin`, `Spearbit`, `ChainSecurity`, `Quantstamp`.
- `auditorLogoUrl`: always `null`. The logo-assets normalizer resolves audit-firm logos after R2 from existing local/cross-protocol cache first, then exact RootData project search, downloads the image under `out/audit-logo/`, and rewrites it to the OneKey static-logo CDN path.
- `date`: report date — `YYYY-MM-DD` or `YYYY-MM`. Bare years like `2024` are invalid. If a GitHub audit folder only shows a year, open the actual report PDF or announcement page to recover the month. If the month truly cannot be determined, use `YYYY-01` and mention the uncertainty in `scope`.
- `scope`: brief description (`Core contracts`, `vePENDLE`, `LP token wrapper`). Null if unknown.
- `reportUrl`: direct PDF or blog post URL.
- `lastScannedAt`: emit any valid `YYYY-MM-DD`; the runner overwrites it before validation.

If you genuinely find no audits, return the empty-audits sentinel in `slice`, plus a single gap explaining why, plus an empty findings array:
```
{
  "slice": { "audits": { "items": [], "lastScannedAt": "1970-01-01" } },
  "findings": [],
  "gaps": [
    { "field": "audits.items", "reason": "no public audit reports found in protocol docs, GitHub, or audit-firm sites", "tried": ["docs/security page", "GitHub /audits repo", "Google site: search of major audit firms"] }
  ],
  "handoff_notes": []
}
```
Do not invent audits to fill the array.

